This paper proposes a new benchmark task for evaluating an agent's abilities to understand natural language and plan on partially observed environments. The task involves navigating through a website to find a specific web page based on a natural language query. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the task involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspects, as the agent needs to efficiently search for relevant information and interact with the website interface.
